
[1]rhapsodist

   RHAP'SODIST, n. [from rhapsody.]

   1. One that writes or speaks without regular dependence of one part of
   his discourse on another.

   2. One who recites or signs rhapsodies for a livelihood; or one who
   makes and repeats verses extempore.

   3. Anciently, one whose profession was to recite the verses of Homer
   and other poets.
